description.$t:
These beautiful girls are the best of friends. They are so close it amazing to see them interact with each other. We are looking for a home for them together.
Luna and Shay where rescued form a home with 4 other adult cats and 17 kittens. They where both amazing Moms and now their babies have been adopted they are looking for a home.
They are very sweet, loving and gentle. Truly awesome girls!!!
They are up to date on vaccines, including rabies, dewormed, treated with revolution, spayed, microchipped and have both tested negative for FIV and Feline Leukemia.
They are come with 6 weeks of pet insurance.

Adoption fee is $350 for the pair.

Watson is a very sweet and gentle neutered male cat.
 
Watson was abandoned by his previous owner at a high kill shelter, we rescued him and he is now looking for his new forever home.

We think he is about 3 years old. He is very sweet and loving. He rolls over like a dog for belly rubs. He has a little bit of a grumpy face but he is not a grumpy boy.
His new foster mom is just getting to know him so we will get up dates as soon as we can. He just arrived on Feb 25.

Watson's adoption fee is $175.00. 
This fee includes - A full physical exam by a Veterinarian, his vaccines, including rabies, neuter, microchip, deworming, treatment with revolution, testing for FIV and Feline Leukemia and 6 weeks of Pet Insurance.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t:
Shiloh and Trey are brother and sister and must be adopted together.
Trey is missing a front leg but it doesn't stop him.

These two have had a very rough start and were removed from their previous home due to neglect. 

They have done amazingly in their new foster home and a full of love. Their foster home is a busy home with 2 young children and Shiloh and Trey fix right in.

Their adoption fee is $350,00 
These two are up to date on their vaccines, have been spayed and neutered, microchipped, dewormed, treated with revolution and tested negative for FIV and Feline Leukemia,

They also come with 6 weeks of Pet Insurance.

Freezie is a very special girl who needs a very special home.

She was found at the side of the road in very rough shape, it has been an 8 month recovery for her but she has recovered and is healthy and save.

She is a street cat and is still unsure of humans but does like to watch them for a far.

She is up to date on vaccines, including rabies, been dewormed and treated with revolution, spayed, microchip and tested negative for FIV and Feline Leukemia.

We are looking for a home that Freezie can just be herself.

Magic is a very sweet boy.
He does need a special family who will understand that he needs some patience to learn to trust people again.

He was found outside, living on the streets and just trying to survive.

Currently he is in a multi cat house hold and we feel it is very important for him to be in a home with other cats so that he can socialize with them. He loves the companionship of other cats.

He is up to date on his vaccines, been neutered, microchip, dewormed and treated with revolution. He also tested negative for FIV and feline leukemia and comes with 6 weeks of pet insurance.
His adoption fee is $175.00

We have kitttens!!!

Cute and cuddly bundles of love.

Males and Females looking for loving homes. All have been in foster homes with other cats, dogs and children

Adoption Fee is $225.00 per kitten. Many of the kittens are Bonded pairs and we will be looking for homes that will adopt them together.

Adoption fee includes, 3 sets of vaccines, including rabies, deworming, spaying or neutering, microchipping and testing for FIV and Feline Leukemia.

Contact us if you are interested and we will e-mail you our adoption application.

Misty Knight and Luke Cage are a bonded brother and sister. They are 5 1/2 months old.
They are very sweet,social, gentle and loving. They love to cuddle together and with their foster family.
They are good with other cats and with children.

Their adoption fee is $450 for the pair. This included their spay and neuter, microchipping, testing for Feline Leukemia and FIV, Deworming, vaccinations including rabies and 6 weeks of pet insurance.

This is Princess Sophie, sister of Bailey. She was rescued from out side. She is a very sweet girl and has really come out of her shell since being brought in. She no longer hides behind the couch in her foster home. She is going to make a wonderful pet. Her adoption fee is $175.00.
She is up to date on her vaccines, including rabies, spayed, microchipped, dewormed, treated with revolution and comes with 6 weeks of pet insurance.

breed.$t: Domestic Long Hair - orange and white

description.$t:
This Beautiful girl's name is Peaches. She is a very sweet, gentle and loving 2 year old female. She was surrendered with her 3 kittens Leo, Stanley and Georgie. 
She is a very playful loving petite girl . 
Peaches adoption fee is $175.00. She is up to date on her vaccines, including Rabies, been spayed, microchipped, dewormed and she tested negative for FIV and Feline Leukemia. She also comes with 6 weeks of pet insurance.

Introducing Bailey.
This sweet little girl was rescued from outside with her sister Princess Sophie. 
She is a beautiful girl who is starting to really come out of her shell. She has come a long way in her foster home and no longer hides behind the couch. She going to make a really wonderful pet.
Her adoption fee is $175.00
She is up to date on her vaccines, including rabies, spayed, microchipped, been dewormed and treated with revolution and comes with 6 weeks of Pet Insurance.

description.$t:
Jeremy  is a loveable sweet cat, rescued from a high-kill animal control unit. A young adult guy, he's a little cautious around new people, taking a little time to warm up - but once he know you, he's very friendly.

He's been to the vet. His shots are up-to-date, he's been dewormed and microchipped and neutered.

The adoption fee for all cats and kittens is $75, or $300 if you decide to adopt two. A gift of six weeks of pre-paid pet health insurance is available.

For more information on Jeremy, please complete an online application form at www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html or email us at denise@actionvolunteersforanimals.com. We try very hard to return phone calls and respond to applications & emails within two days.

description.$t:
Gabby is a friendly georgeous dilute calico.  She was rescued from a high kill shelter.  Gabby does not however like other cats, so she must be adopted as a single cat.  She is vaccinated, microchipped and spayed.  She is also very playful, and loves catnip treats and her toys.  She would make a wonderful companion.  

The adoption fee for all cats and kittens is $175, or $300 if you decide to adopt two. A gift of six weeks of pre-paid pet health insurance is available.

For more information on Gabby, please complete an online application form at www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html or email us at denise@actionvolunteersforanimals.com.

description.$t:
Jessie was rescued from a snow making machine before the coldest weather hit this past winter. We had an idea this kitty was tame , as we could hear her crying in the snow making machine. Jessie was assumed by the vet to be about 7 years old.... that is, until her microchip was discovered and we realized she is 13 years old. The microchip could not be traced. Jessie would prefer to go to a quiet household, perhaps to live with a senior, single person, or quiet couple.

She has been spayed, vaccinated, and vet-checked.

If you are interested in adopting Jessie, please complete an online application form at our web-site: http://www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html. You may also contact our adoption coordinator at denise@actionvolunteersforanimals.com. We try very hard to respond to applications and e-mails within 2 business days.

description.$t:
Declawed...Can cope with dogs!.....Interested? Please complete our online application form found at :
www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html

AVA is looking for that extra special home and family for a special girl.  Gabby needs a home where she will be accepted and loved for just who she is.  She needs a home that will give her time (possibly months) to adjust and feel accepted.  She is not a lap cat but likes to be patted and spoken to. She is an observer of life and because she is not often a very active participant she has a bit of a weight problem.  She has been on a diet in her foster home and has recently lost a pound.  Her attending Vet will be happy to hear that.
 
Gabby has a beautiful face and lovely eyes.  She is in good health except for a few extra pounds.  Her recent bloodwork is perfect.  She was declawed (in the past -- not by AVA) and has medium length blue/grey hair which she likes to have brushed.  Gabby is about 5 to 6 years old.  She gets along fine with other cats and dogs too.
 
We are hoping to find a home that will continue to help Gabby with her weight loss plan and will give her lots of time to become part of their family.

description.$t:
Interested?  If so please complete our online application form found at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html  We'll get back to you within 24 hours...

Simba was taken from the streets of Tehran, Iran when she was about 2 months old. She was hit by a car and ended up with broken legs.  A kind person took her to the vet and kept her until she was perfectly fine again but she couldn't place her in Iran so she sent her to Canada to her friend 

Simba is now a year old.  She has all her vaccinations, and is micro-chipped. Simba is also very playful.  She is good with other cats and would be fine with older children only..

Owen is a very friendly, sweet boy, who gets along well with other cats. He was rescued from a high kill animal shelter. He has been neutered, de-wormed, de-flead and microchipped, and shots, including rabies, are up-to-date.   

The adoption fee for all cats and kittens is $175, or 300 if you decide to adopt two. A gift of six weeks of pre-paid pet health insurance is available.

For more information on our sweet boy, please complete an online application form at www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html or email us at denise@actionvolunteersforanimals.com. We try very hard to return phone calls and respond to applications & emails within two days.

description.$t:
Joel is a lovely black cat with a beautiful shine to his fur.  Once he gets to know you he is extremely affectionate, though may be a bit shy at first.  He is a lap cat and is very easy to handle and gentle.  

Joel is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped.  Joel is fine with other cats. 

The adoption fee for all cats and kittens is $175, or $300 if you decide to adopt two. A gift of six weeks of pre-paid pet health insurance is available.

For more information on Joel, please complete an online application form at www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html or email us at denise@actionvolunteersforanimals.com.  We try very hard to return phone calls and respond to applications & emails within two days.

Cherry and her siblings were trapped and about to be euthanized when our rescue group managed to save them.  Being born outside they were not used to humans.  Cherry is now the most wonderful girl, loves pets and cuddles and plays constantly. She wants to be with her foster family all the time. She is still shy in new situations and with new people so if you are prepared to be patient and spend time with Cherry she is adorable and will make the best companion ever!


Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Linden was trapped with her family and about to be euthanized when they were all rescued.  She was born in a garden and never socialized so sometimes she is still a little nervous in new situations.  But quickly adapts and now loves to be petted ad play with humans and other cats.  Linden loves to get lots of attention. She is a beautiful tabby with lovely green eyes.  If you have a little time to spend with her she will be a wonderful companion.  Linden would like to be adopted with one of her sisters (Ivy or Cherry) or to a home with another young friendly cat.


Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Gabriella (Gabi) was relinquished to us from a family who could no longer keep her.  We don't know what her life was like before coming to our rescue, but she arrived very skinny, shy and very scared.  She is trusting more and more and now even plays a little.  She loves her food and treats and gentle pats.  Gabi needs a quiet home with a family who is aware she may have been traumatized in the past.  A family with the patience and time to give her all the love and attention she needs to become a well adjusted cat.
Gabi is doing great in her foster home as she feels safe and loved but she needs a forever home of her own.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Faye was rescued at 1 year old, expecting kittens.  She had 6 babies just like her.   All have grown into beautiful cats as she looked after them so well and most have found their forever homes.

Faye really needs a home of her own, without other pets or young children.  She is extremely loveable and enjoys pats, being held and just snuggling with her foster family.  She also goes crazy for toys and plays like mad.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Glenice at 905-683-0459

Sarah is a very sweet girl.  She loves pats and hanging out with humans.  She can be a little shy at first but is very devoted when she gets to know you. She also loves toys, climbing and playing with her brother.   Sarah needs to find a home with her brother Prince as they are very bonded.


Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Glenice at 905-683-0459

Prince is very affectionate.  He is also very busy and curious and wants to be part of the action.  Loves his toys and lots of playing and attention.  Prince needs to find a home with his sister Sarah.  They are very bonded and follow each other everywhere.


Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Neuter, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Glenice at 905-683-0459

address1.$t: Taunton Rd. and Harmony Rd., Oshawa

description.$t:
In January 2016, sweet Suzy found her way into A.V.A's care after being rescued as a stray. As she began adjusting to the luxurious life of an indoor cat at her foster home, her beautiful personality has started to shine through.

Suzy has a very calm disposition and is very quiet. She enjoys sitting back and watching what everyone is up to in the house! 

As she has become more comfortable and confident, we've discovered Suzy also has a comical and sneaky side to her! ( video attached to profile)

Suzy loves to be pet and she will roll over to get some good belly rubs from you too!

She is being fostered in a home with cats and dogs but flourishes when things are quieter.

She has been spayed, microchipped and is up to date on her shots.

If you are looking for a sweet and calm cat Suzy is your girl.

Adoption fee is $175.00 or $300.00 for a pair.

To learn more about her please contact denise.avadurham@gmail.com or you can fill out an online adoption form: http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html,
